assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: New Japan Chemical Co., Ltd. produces and sells chemical products in Japan and internationally. The company provides oleo-chemicals, including hydrogenated oils, fatty acids, esters, glycerin, alcohols, non-ionic and anion surfactants, and amino acid-based and amphoteric surfactants; and plasticizer, such as phthalate and non-phthalate plasticizers, and specialty plasticizers. It also offers plastic and coating materials, which include crystalline nucleating and epoxy resin curing agent, epoxy resin, monomers, methacrylate, and antistatic agents; and lubricants, such as low evaporation and viscosity oil, dibasic acid esters, and aromatic oils. The company was incorporated in 1919 and is headquartered in Osaka, Japan.
